annotationA: Tyrosine--tRNA ligase, mitochondrial; Catalyzes the attachment of tyrosine to tRNA(Tyr) in a two-step reaction: tyrosine is first activated by ATP to form Tyr- AMP and then transferred to the acceptor end of tRNA(Tyr); Belongs to the class-I aminoacyl-tRNA synthetase family
annotationB: Tryptophanyl-tRNA synthetase, mitochondrial, isoform A; ATP binding; tryptophan-tRNA ligase activity. It is involved in the biological process described with: tryptophanyl-tRNA aminoacylation
